metadata.name: GEOMETRIC #58
metadata.description:
Following the search for formal simplification, where everything is built using simple geometric figures, aggregations to planes and colors, lights and shadows.

Features:
PALLETS
In total, the work has 31 different color palettes, with probability percentages ranging from 2% to 7%.

FORMS
The images are structured using just four simple shapes (square, rectangle, circle and triangle) proportional to each other.

The use of each of the forms follows six different combination patterns.

VECTOR
Rectangular elements can have two orientations (horizontal or vertical).

SATURATION
In total, four levels of color saturation are applied, ranging from 25% to 100%.

CANVAS
Altogether there are four different canvas formats, in the following proportions: 1x2, 2x3, 3x4 and 1x1.

FRAGMENTATION AND DENSITY
Finally, the elements are combined from four stages of fragmentation and five levels of density.

November 14, 2022.

Paivei's generative token made with p5js, in celebration of the first anniversary of FxHash.

 #fxhashturnsone

metadata.name: The String #159
metadata.description:
|| Anniversary project for FX(hash) 1st birthday ||

Each virtual object consists of 365 lights.
Each light represents one day of the year.

We go through every single day, thinking it's all crucial. Yet, from a perspective, it all gets compressed into a single thread. Some of the events are brighter and more memorable. Others just blend or fade away.

I welcomed November 2021 with huge excitement and celebration. The joyful beginning of the month was followed by weeks of misery, anxiety, denial, and acceptance. It was a hard time, but in the long run, it was liberating and started a process of change. Change that happens dynamically to this day.

I couldn't join you last year, but I'm celebrating with you today!



In memory of my Dad.



Donations:
40% – Savepakistan - Flood Relief Fundraiser
10% – Three.js

metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #179
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License

GPU intensive

metadata.name: Cables and Clouds #72
metadata.description:
Capturing clouds... an old dream of mad scientist... coming true...
But wait... are they real clouds ? Maybe... maybe not...
Is it the real life ?
Is this just fantasy ?

Interaction.
Press h in live mode to list the possibilities.
Key 's'  : Save an image of the output at the current resolution
Key 1-9 : Change resolution
Key 'c' to change color palette
Key 'd' to toggle a special color mode to highlight the different components (and have the number of points used in your specific drawing).

Features.
18 different features displayed (format, color palettes, main elements characteristics, rare elements...).

metadata.name: MONOLITH #43
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_
